00:39:14,191 --> 00:39:18,254
[SPEAKER_10]: I didn't have to be a son of the Pentacook, Quinnipiac, or Mohican.

280
00:39:19,154 --> 00:39:24,398
[SPEAKER_10]: I didn't have to have a pilgrim pedigree or be a Connecticut Yankee from King Arthur's Court.

281
00:39:25,179 --> 00:39:31,123
[SPEAKER_10]: I can be the Dahomian, the Pole, or the child of Caribbean suns and Amazon shades.

282
00:39:33,405 --> 00:39:34,766
[SPEAKER_10]: I can love this country too.

283
00:39:35,486 --> 00:39:39,328
[SPEAKER_10]: My green card was a welcome ticket to a new life in a new land.

284
00:39:39,928 --> 00:39:42,969
[SPEAKER_10]: My passport was stamped with new hopes and new dreams.

285
00:39:43,049 --> 00:39:49,312
[SPEAKER_10]: My suitcase was packed full with new aspirations and some apprehensions too.

286
00:39:59,918 --> 00:40:09,121
[SPEAKER_10]: Perhaps I didn't see the harbor sign that said, give me your tired, your poor, your huddled masses yearning to breathe free, the wretched refuge of your teeming shore.

287
00:40:09,201 --> 00:40:12,161
[SPEAKER_10]: Send these, the homeless, tempest-tossed to me.

288
00:40:12,582 --> 00:40:15,142
[SPEAKER_10]: I lift my lamp beside the golden door.

289
00:40:15,942 --> 00:40:24,925
[SPEAKER_10]: Perhaps I didn't see the lady in the lamp, but I did see the gleaming city on a hill that couldn't be hid, and my soul responded.

290
00:40:27,734 --> 00:40:29,175
[SPEAKER_10]: I can love this country, too.

291
00:40:30,035 --> 00:40:33,276
[SPEAKER_10]: I can love its rocky mountains and its rolling meadows.

292
00:40:34,057 --> 00:40:37,938
[SPEAKER_10]: I can love its gospel songs and its crazy rhythms.

293
00:40:38,818 --> 00:40:42,560
[SPEAKER_10]: I can love its asphalt highways and its born-to-run boss.

294
00:40:43,460 --> 00:40:47,342
[SPEAKER_10]: I can love its teeming ghetto and its urban sprawl.

295
00:40:48,082 --> 00:40:53,224
[SPEAKER_10]: I can love its old spires, new minarets, and golden menorahs.

296
00:41:03,772 --> 00:41:03,892
do

297
00:41:29,369 --> 00:41:31,211
[SPEAKER_10]: But can America love me, too?

298
00:41:32,213 --> 00:41:35,357
[SPEAKER_10]: Can she love my curry spices, roti, and oxtails?

299
00:41:36,478 --> 00:41:39,502
[SPEAKER_10]: Can she love my dearie, akjonjon, and papitas?

300
00:41:40,523 --> 00:41:42,944
[SPEAKER_10]: Can she love my hijab and henna tattoos?

301
00:41:42,984 --> 00:41:47,026
[SPEAKER_10]: Can she love my Hajj, my Mecca, my Medina?

302
00:41:47,686 --> 00:41:50,828
[SPEAKER_10]: Can she love my Cinco de Mayo, my Dia de los Muertos?

303
00:41:50,888 --> 00:41:55,290
[SPEAKER_10]: Can she love my kente cloth, dreads, twists, and locks?

304
00:41:56,150 --> 00:42:04,714
[SPEAKER_10]: Can she love the skin I'm in, be it ebony, ivory, dulce de leche, or cafe au lait?

305
00:42:06,485 --> 00:42:08,526
[SPEAKER_10]: Can she love me by name?

306
00:42:09,246 --> 00:42:20,831
[SPEAKER_10]: Shekinah Glory, Muhammad Bin Saeed, Anastasia Kozov, Cleophis Dorsey, Claudia Gonzalez, or Gael Petit Frere, can she love me by name?

307
00:42:22,552 --> 00:42:29,495
[SPEAKER_10]: And what if I am among those huddled masses in that wretched refuge or that homeless, tempest-tossed?

308
00:42:30,475 --> 00:42:32,536
[SPEAKER_10]: Will she continue to lift her lamp?

309
00:42:35,572 --> 00:42:49,769
[SPEAKER_10]: or do war and rumors of war, IEDs, sleeper cells, and faith distortions make me a pariah to be eliminated, a scourge to be annihilated, and a plague to be exterminated.

310
00:42:53,132 --> 00:42:54,033
[SPEAKER_10]: I come in peace.

311
00:42:57,023 --> 00:42:58,184
[SPEAKER_10]: I love this country, too.

312
00:42:58,985 --> 00:43:00,766
[SPEAKER_10]: I love its boundless opportunity.

313
00:43:00,846 --> 00:43:03,128
[SPEAKER_10]: I love its generosity of spirit.

314
00:43:03,208 --> 00:43:05,249
[SPEAKER_10]: I love the audacity of its hope.

315
00:43:05,670 --> 00:43:08,452
[SPEAKER_10]: I love its rolling meadows and its joyful songs.

316
00:43:08,852 --> 00:43:12,575
[SPEAKER_10]: I love its asphalt highways and its little red Corvette.

317
00:43:13,596 --> 00:43:17,539
[SPEAKER_10]: I love its teeming ghetto and its urban sprawl.

318
00:43:18,760 --> 00:43:23,744
[SPEAKER_10]: I love its old spires, new minarets, and golden menorahs.

319
00:43:25,925 --> 00:43:30,307
[SPEAKER_10]: I come in peace and I love America too.

320
00:43:31,188 --> 00:43:36,110
[SPEAKER_10]: I come in peace and I love America too.

321
00:43:46,755 --> 00:43:47,255
[SPEAKER_10]: Thank you.

322
00:43:48,896 --> 00:43:49,356
[SPEAKER_10]: Thank you.

