[SPEAKER_10]: At last year's MLK celebration back on 111 Arlington Street, a little bit smaller than today's,

334
00:44:58,900 --> 00:45:06,102
[SPEAKER_10]: We began a new WMC tradition to honor community leadership in a number of important areas.

335
00:45:07,602 --> 00:45:19,445
[SPEAKER_10]: We awarded the first Drum Major Awards, picking up on Dr. King's notion of leading out and being engaged in the business of building beloved community.

336
00:45:20,405 --> 00:45:34,412
[SPEAKER_10]: Today's second annual WMCC Drum Major Awards focus on the categories of community advocacy, dedicated public service, and cultural legacy.

337
00:45:35,092 --> 00:45:39,214
[SPEAKER_10]: Here to help me present those awards are Lisa Crossman,

338
00:45:59,133 --> 00:46:07,637
[SPEAKER_10]: West Med Community Center Incorporated is honored to present the 2024 Drum Major Award to Joseph M. Jones.

339
00:46:34,358 --> 00:46:59,997
[SPEAKER_10]: in view of your cultural and social significance to the West Medford community and to greater Medford as a builder of bridges, a peacemaker, a preserver of neighborhood history, an active volunteer, a mentor, a teacher, and an outstanding role model for young people, we gratefully present this acknowledgement.

340
00:47:00,558 --> 00:47:01,719
[SPEAKER_10]: You will always

341
00:47:02,139 --> 00:47:08,647
[SPEAKER_10]: have an honored place in the annals and living archive of your beloved neighborhood home.

342
00:47:09,228 --> 00:47:16,457
[SPEAKER_10]: Presented this day, signed by Lisa M. Crossman, Executive Director, January 15, 2024, West Medford Community Center.

343
00:47:23,615 --> 00:47:28,037
